black anger erupted into violence four 
times in the last decade but now black lawyers are leading a 
quiet riot an economic boycott that is costing millions of 
tourist dollars 
the activists were aggrieved by local governments handling of 
antiapartheid leader nelson mandelas visit in june 
instead of enthusiastic welcomes and ceremonies mandela received 
elsewhere on his us visit he got an official snub and criticism 
