<TEXT>
women who have had silicone breast implants 
seem to agree on one thing that people considering this procedure 
need more information and the implants themselves need better 
safety testing 
a panel of women told of their experiences with implants before 
a house subcommittee tuesday urging action that ranged from a 
moratorium on the sale of implants to an appeal to keep options 
open for women who want their breasts reconstructed after cancer 
surgery 
sybil niden goldrich of beverly hills calif said the two sets 
of implants she had have left her with a silicone sword of 
damocles hanging over my head 
ive gone seven years without a recurrence of breast cancer 
but what will happen from the silicone she said at the house 
government operations human resources subcommittee hearing i 
shudder when i think about it 
the first implants left her with a body rash pain fever 
rockhard breasts and gynecological problems they were 
replaced with another set but the problems continued these 
implants were removed also and she had her breasts reconstructed 
in a different procedure using her own body tissue 
her gynecological problems continued and she had a hysterectomy 
two years ago a biopsy of her liver at the time identified 
silicone she said 
i encourage you to demand a moratorium on the sale of these 
products until we are absolutely certain that the safety of these 
implants can be proven beyond reasonable doubt she said 
silicone breast implants have been used since the early 1960s 
they have been placed in about 2 million american women and are 
implanted at the rate of about 130000 a year 
when 1976 amendments to the food drug and cosmetic act required 
regulation of medical devices breast implants were 
grandfathered into the market this meant they did not have to 
meet the specifications required of new products 
the food and drug administration has classified silicone 
implants as high risk but it has not yet finalized a regulation 
that would require manufacturers to submit safety data or remove 
their products from the market fda officials testified the rule 
would be made final in march 
rep ted weiss dny chairman of the subcommittee said he 
was concerned about the inordinate delay and seven years of 
the agency dragging its feet especially in light of the 
unanswered questions about silicone implants 
another implant recipient rosemary locke director of a womens 
breast cancer support program in the washington dc area gave the 
panel a different perspective 
locke who had a double mastectomy and reconstruction said she 
had some complications after surgery but explained that having my 
body restored eased away much of the trauma of breast cancer 
i have never regretted my decision even though i now know 
more about silicone implants than when i made my decision she 
said 
she urged the subcommittee and the fda as they consider breast 
implants please keep in mind the women who have lost breasts to 
cancer silicone implants may be their only option for surgically 
restoring their body 
dow corning corp one of the largest makers of silicone breast 
implants distributed a survey by the american society of plastic 
and reconstructive surgeons that found 92 percent of women with 
breast augmentation or reconstruction said they were satisfied with 
their implant surgery 
about 25 percent of silicone breast implants are for breast 
reconstruction after breast cancer surgery the rest are for breast 
enlargement 
the fda has received 2017 reports of adverse reactions from 
silicone implants said walter gundaker acting director of the 
fdas center for devices and radiological health 
about 3000 other such reports are from salinefilled breast 
implants which are less common than silicone ones however the 
saline implants also contain silicone 
witnesses at the hearing said these numbers were conservative 
because many physicians and surgeons do not report the problems 
