<TEXT>
a judge today dismissed charges against a 
man accused of sexually assaulting a woman with 46 personalities 
after a prosecutor said a retrial would harm her 
winnebago county district attorney joe paulus said he decided 
against prosecuting 29yearold mark a peterson again after 
doctors for the 27yearold victim said the ordeal of another trial 
likely would cause her mental condition to worsen 
a jury convicted peterson nov 8 of seconddegree sexual assault 
but the judge threw out the verdict monday and ordered another 
trial the judge decided that peterson received an unfair trial 
because his psychiatrist was not allowed to examine the woman 
whose name has not been used to protect her identity 
it is clear that a new trial would not be in the best 
interests of the victim and in fact may cause her additional 
harm paulus wrote in a letter to winnebago county circuit judge 
robert hawley 
hawley signed an order this morning dismissing the charge of 
seconddegree sexual assault against peterson said winnebago 
county deputy district attorney vince biskupic 
it is a crime in wisconsin for someone to have sex with a 
mentally ill person who cannot understand the consequences of their 
actions the perpetrator must also know the person is mentally ill 
the jury ruled peterson a married exgrocery store bagger 
manipulated one of the womans personalities to have sex with her 
in the front seat of his car two days after they met 
paulus said the woman was willing to go through another trial 
but he told the judge in a letter that he consulted with three 
medical experts on multiple personality disorder and they advised 
against another trial 
one of the primary goals of the prosecution of mark peterson 
was to protect the rights of a mentally ill woman and hold her 
attacker accountable under the law paulus said 
the jury verdict although now set aside on a legal 
technicality sent a strong message to the community that mentally 
ill individuals in our society must be protected from those who 
prey upon them 
since the case became public the victims personalities have 
grown from 18 to 21 to 46 police were called to her home after she 
reported one personality was trying to kill her she has been under 
constant psychiatric care and has been hospitalized 
