<TEXT>
here are excerpts from recent editorials in newspapers in the 
united states and abroad 
 
dec 16 
the sun herald gulfport miss on congress 
businesses and industries are tightening their belts cutting 
back on expansion plans freezing salaries and payrolls reducing 
expenses and in some cases laying off workers the people in 
congress in contrast arent troubling themselves with such 
recessionfighting steps 
why should congressmen and women worry the business of 
government is booming senators fresh from getting a raise to 
98400 last february look forward to january when they will get 
the next pay raise they gave themselves this one to 101900 
representatives did themselves even better jumping their paychecks 
from 96600 to 125100 
lest you should think that those increases arent enough 
compensation for the wonderful job the congress is doing remember 
that senators will be allowed to keep up to 23837 in honoraria 
the fees for giving speeches writing articles and similar 
moonlighting house members will stop keeping honoraria 
one other note about the pay increases congressfolk achieved 
them without accountability it was done by voice vote no names 
recorded no fingerprints or footprints no individual 
accountability no need to defend a yea vote since the individuals 
voices were lost in the chorus 
next year congress will cost about 22 billion the cost has 
gone up by almost 2 billion in the last 20 years the climb upward 
has been as steadily and as surely as the rise in the national 
debt 
 
dec 14 
toledo ohio blade on limiting congressional terms 
the throwtherascalsout brigade received a boost when 
president bush added his voice to those calling for term limits for 
members of congress 
bush is climbing upon a bandwagon that is not yet rolling 
voters in november indicated that they do not yet have a specific 
idea of how term limits will be achieved or what duration terms 
should be although 12 years is most often suggested rather there 
is a distinct hankering for change for somebody to do 
something to improve the way our system of government is or is 
not working 
we understand that sentiment of course the notion of the 
citizenlegislator as a publicspirited individual who serves his 
or her state or district for a limited period and then returns to 
private life is appealing it points to politics as a calling a 
responsibility to be shouldered not as a sinecure with a good 
pension 
quality leadership conscientious lawmakers representatives 
expert in their field and diligent in performing their duties would 
be thrown out arbitrarily with the rascals 
even so term limits reflect the groundswell of obvious public 
distaste for the game of politics it should not be ignored 
 
dec 18 
chicago tribune on nasa 
even before the shuttle challenger blew apart shortly after 
launch in 1986 there were signs that the nations space program 
was drifting off course 
critics hoped the challenger accident would spark thorough 
selfexamination and new direction at the national aeronautics and 
space administration but recent troubles flaws in the hubble 
space telescope fuel leaks in the aging shuttle fleet and 
controversy over a planned space station suggest the program 
still lacks a sound flight plan 
a panel of experts has offered the white house a strong 
sensible proposal to get americas space exploration back on the 
right path 
in addition to being drafted with singular political sensitivity 
and shrewdness the proposals together set clear logical 
objectives for a new space era one defined primarily by federal 
budget deficits and the end of the cold war the first will mean 
maximizing the available resources to achieve agreedupon goals 
the second should lead to greater international cooperation and a 
reduced military role in space 
the 12member committee called for sweeping overhaul of the 
space program specifically it proposed that the space shuttle be 
largely replaced by a new family of powerful unmanned rockets it 
called for a major redesign and simplification of the space station 
aimed at lowering its 37 billion price tag 
and instead of concentrating on engineering feats and highly 
visible missions with limited practical value the panel would make 
scientific research on the earth and its environment the top 
priority 
this is the correct approach in the postcold war tightbudget 
era it can also regenerate interest in space exploration 
directing peoples imagination and enterprise toward new frontiers 
and achievements 
 
dec 12 
daily times primos pa on nasa 
the space shuttles future is up in the air if were 
interpreting signals from the government correctly 
the same nation that put a man on the moon is now trying to put 
the beleagured space shuttle in the garage a 12member space 
panel which was formed after nasas embarrassments began piling 
up has recommended that space shuttle flights be confined only 
to those that require human involvement 
lets face it the space shuttle program has had its share of 
troubles this year 
the panel also suggested that nasa go back to the drawing board 
and redesign its proposed space station and rethink its priorities 
one thing for certain is that whatever lies in nasas future it 
cant be much if nasas space exploration program in this case 
the shuttle is relegated to just a few flights all of which would 
be one giant step backward for mankind 
space travel is and will never be free of risks we have known 
and understood that for years 
 
dec 13 
the waco texas tribuneherald on young smokers 
the tobacco industry has launched a program to discourage 
children from taking up cigarette smoking the industry campaign 
supports state laws limiting cigarette sales to adults and puts new 
limitations on billboard advertising near schools 
the tobacco industry campaign is as far as it goes a worthy 
effort to prevent american youths from picking up a hazardous habit 
that can lead to death 
congress and state legislatures should not let the tobacco 
industry campaign sway them from passage of legislation that would 
further protect the health and lives of millions of americans 
hooked on smoking 
smoking is a serious health hazard and governmental bodies have 
the responsibility to take all reasonable steps to protect citizens 
from health hazards 
 
</TEXT>
