he said the number of people using illicit drugs was down 44 
percent over the past five years from 23 million in 1985 to 129 
million in 1990 
the news we have today sugggests that our hard work is paying 
off bush said he spoke briefly at a news conference called to 
release the 1990 national household survey on drug abuse 
