<TEXT>
nasa scientists pretending to be 
explorers from another world said wednesday they had concluded life 
exists on earth and it may be intelligent 
the scientists based their conclusinon on data from the 
jupiterbound galileo spacecraft 
the accumulated evidence we have would give your 
hypothetical explorer a very strong indication you had biological 
activity on earth said torrence johnson galileos chief 
scientist at the jet propulsion laboratory 
galileos study of earth illustrates how researchers use data 
collected by spacecraft to reach conclusions about other planets 
galileo boomeranged past earth and the moon dec 8 using the 
planets gravity as a slingshot to speed it up and expand its orbit 
around the sun so it can reach jupiter in 1995 
scientists used the opportunity to treat earth as an alien 
planet ordering galileo to snap a few thousand pictures and make 
numerous measurements they outlined their findings during a 
wednesday news conference 
measurements made by galileos infrared lightdetecting 
instrument showed earths atmosphere is rich in nitrous oxide 
methane and oxygen indicating theres a lot of life on the 
planet said laboratory scientist robert w carlson 
another of galileos instruments picked up nonnatural radio 
signals that got stronger closer to the planet which would make 
alien scientists strongly suspect earth has intelligent life that 
makes radio broadcasts johnson said 
the spaceship also detected lightning bolts made measurements 
to help explain creation of the northern and southern lights 
determined the planet is warmed by a mild greenhouse effect and 
detected a highaltitude ice cloud that helps cause the annual hole 
in the protective ozone layer over antarctica 
on the moon galileo found evidence of a huge volcanic eruption 
4 billion years ago that shows such volcanic activity occurred 
about 200 million years earlier than previously believed said 
brown university geologist jim head 
the spacecrafts pictures also confirmed the existence of a 
1200milewide meteorite impact basin on the southern hemisphere 
of the moons far side the largest such crater ever identified 
head said 
the national aeronautics and space administration released nine 
more of galileos photos of the earth and moon wednesday 
one was a mosaic assembled from 11 separate pictures showing 
all of icy antarctica others showed huge lunar craters a color 
map of minerals on the moons surface clouds swirling over south 
america and australias larger lakes and great barrier reef 
the pictures didnt display evidence of life on earth because 
galileos closest approach to the planet at a distance of 597 
miles was over the southwest atlantic ocean the detail in the 
pictures was inadequate to reveal buildings scientists said 
nasa also displayed two short movies made by assembling 
hundreds of galileos still photos showing the earth and moon 
spinning 
top that ted turner head declared after the colorized 
lunar movie was played he was referring to media mogul turners 
controversial practice of colorizing classic films 
also wednesday galileo fired its thrusters repeatedly to aim 
itself properly for its close encounter with the asteroid gaspra 
next oct 29 said project manager bill oneil 
galileo will swing past earth again dec 8 1992 for a final 
gravity slingshot maneuver to help it reach jupiter in july 
1995 galileo will separate into an orbiter and a probe both will 
reach jupiter in december 1995 
the probe will descend into jupiters atmosphere returning data 
to the orbiter until the probe is crushed by intense atmospheric 
pressure the orbiter will circle jupiter for at least two years 
studying the planet and making closeup pictures of its 10 largest 
moons 
</TEXT>
