the maximum penalty for bribery is 10 years imprisonment and a 
fine of 250000 
the maximum penalty for interstate travel in aid of racketeering 
and giving false statements is five years in prison and a 250000 
fine 
a conviction for tax fraud could bring three years imprisonment 
and a fine of 250000 
another wideranging undercover probe centered in chicago was 
dubbed operation greylord in which fbi agents posed as corrupt 
attorneys to gather evidence on lawyers and cook county judges 
more than 90 people including 15 judges were convicted 
since 1978 more than 400 public officials in chicago have been 
convicted on corruption charges 
