<TEXT>
mbongeni ngemas sarafina celebrated the 
courageous schoolchildren of soweto the black south african 
enclave that exploded in rebellion against an oppressive white 
government in 1976 
the unusual and often exuberant musical was a surprise success 
at lincoln center three years ago it later moved to broadway for a 
long run and is still touring 
now ngema is back in new york with another musical for lincoln 
center theater but this time the company has found its way to the 
majestic an old movie house off flatbush avenue in brooklyn where 
director peter brook presented his mahabharata and the cherry 
orchard 
the crumbling film palace deliberately left in a state of 
semidecay is an evocative home for township fever ngemas 
latest effort which is done in conjunction with the brooklyn 
academy of music the shabby surroundings complement a shantytown 
of corrugated iron huts strung across the wide stage 
but the show which runs about half an hour too long is not as 
consistently stirring as sarafina thats because its more 
polemical moments are stridently or broadly dramatized and might 
have been more effective if sung or danced 
but when the music takes over township fever manages to be 
as heartfelt as its precedessor exuding a theatricality that 
reinforces the shows antiapartheid message 
in township fever rebellion is again in the air yet the 
musical which opened wednesday takes a more ambiguous approach 
than sarafina to another turbulent episode in the history of 
modernday south africa ngemas new work looks at black vs black 
in a world where the rules are set by the white minority heroes 
and villains are not so easily defined 
the musical puts on stage the 1987 strike by black railway 
workers of the south african transport services ngema personalizes 
the events telling them through a young man named jazz his 
girlfriend tonko and best friend and eventual betrayer 
philadelphia 
during the walkout several scabs who go to work for the 
railroad are murdered by strikers it is the leading characters 
friend who fingers the killers today facing death sentences they 
are still in jail 
ngema not only wrote the book music and lyrics for township 
fever but he directed and choreographed the show as well hes 
the one who must take responsibility for lag in interest between 
the song and dance 
still township fever soars during those musical moments 
most of them done in mbaqanga a type of rock music infused with 
jazz and found in south african townships the score is infectious 
and rousingly sung by a large cast particularly brian mazibuko as 
the doomed hero and sindiswa dlathu as his true love they get 
strong help from a distinctive supporting cast as well as from a 
large onstage orchestra that peers out from behind those township 
hovels 
the dancing has the same vitality found in sarafina one 
wishes there were more of it particularly because the choreography 
allows designer sarah roberts to show off a colorful array of 
exotic costumes 
but for the most part in township fever the message is in 
the music and when they come together it makes for a stirring 
evening of theater 
