investors are seizing on what they perceive as a buying 
opportunity 
the memory is still fresh in their minds analysts reason of 
the profits that awaited most people who stepped up to buy in the 
aftermath of the crash in 87 
some skeptics see this is as a danger sign typically they say 
bear markets dont bottom out until mutualfund investors have been 
scared away in large numbers 
optimistic observers by contrast say it could be a sign that 
fund investors have learned to think longerterm building up their 
holdings in good times and bad 
