new film could revive the career of george hamilton and boost 
brigid fonda and franc dambrosio the opera singer making his film 
debut as pacinos son 
the godfather was a 1972 phenomenon not only because it 
amassed more money than any previous film but also for its 
starmaking capacities pacino who had made only one previous film 
panic in needle park became an immediate star the same was 
true with diane keaton in her second film after looking for mr 
goodbar 
robert duvall had been playing smaller roles since to kill a 
mockingbird in 1964 his role as the consigliere elevated him to 
stardom both keaton and duvall went on to win academy awards 
james caan was already a popular actor but his role as the 
hotheaded sonny corleone in the first two films provided a big 
boost 
