<TEXT>
it is a bittersweet season in america a pause at the edge of 
war the nation has embraced hostages newly released soldiers soon 
to depart and memories of those already gone to the persian gulf 
with some urgency families have drawn especially close in the 
knowledge that neither home for the holidays nor peace on earth can 
be presumed 
theres anxiety and loneliness said patricia enninga whose 
son is in the persian gulf with the armys 82nd airborne division 
people are trying to grab onto whatever they can but 
everything keeps changing 
saddam hussein says he wont let go of kuwait president bush 
stands firm behind his line in the sand between them lies jan 15 
