<TEXT>
a federal judge has confirmed 
wheelingpittsburgh steel corps reorganization plan ending five 
years of litigation 
us bankruptcy judge warren bentz on tuesday signed the order 
that will allow the company to stay in business 
wheelingpittsburgh employs about 7100 people at six major plants 
in western pennsylvania ohio and west virginia 
bentz said dec 8 he intended to approve the plan he made the 
announcement after two days of hearings into objections filed by 
the farmers home administration and the us environmental 
protection agency 
under the reorganization plan about 600 million in cash will 
be distributed to creditors company officials said plan 
proponents say the reorganization is viable and will allow the 
company to compete 
the plan creates two corporations one is wheelingpittsburgh 
corp a holding company led by new york investor ronald labow who 
bought 86 percent of the companys secured debt the other is 
wheelingpittsburgh steel corp an operating subsidiary 
company officials have said the company plans a 454 million 
capital improvement program over the next five years 
