<TEXT>
britains economy shrank 12 percent in the third 
quarter the biggest contraction in 10 years the government said 
wednesday 
the central statistical office said a cut in oil production was 
to blame for the drop in its average estimate of gross domestic 
product 
the treasurys top official meanwhile said the outlook was for 
a weak performance in the fourth quarter of 1990 and early 1991 
but chancellor of the exchequer norman lamont told a yearend 
briefing of foreign journalists that the current slowdown is a 
desirable byproduct of years of rapid expansion 
although companies and industries undoubtedly will suffer from a 
slowdown this is the price you pay to get inflation down he 
said 
lamont predicted the downturn would not last as long as 
britains 198081 recession 
