mannesmann ag said wednesday it is 
forming a joint venture with digital equipment corp that will give 
digital effective control over the german companys computer 
operations 
the transaction ends mannesmanns lengthy search for a partner 
for its computer units which have seen their profits slide at the 
same time it provides digital with a greater presence in europe 
especially in the field of industrial computer applications 
under the terms of the agreement mannesmann will spin off the 
computer operations of its mannesmann kienzle gmbh division into a 
jointly owned company digitalkienzle computersysteme 
digital will pay about 230 million for a 65 percent stake in 
that company which would be digitals biggest external investment 
ever the announcement said 
mannesmanns computer units have annual sales of about 540 
million their profit dropped sharply last year to about 24 
million from 154 million the year before 
the german subsidiary of digital had revenue of 835 million in 
its fiscal 1990 which ended june 30 
digital equipment based in maynard mass had worldwide 
revenue of 129 billion in its fiscal 1990 
