<TEXT>
what would a mcdonalds corp restaurant 
call an experimental submarine sandwich obviously its the mcsub 
the fastfood giant which recently beefed up its menu with 
pizzas and specialty sandwiches has given five outlets in this 
college town permission to try their luck with the mcsubs 
the test reflects a desire by restaurants near the university of 
wisconsin to find a product tailored to students and is not being 
promoted by the corporation said carol koepke mcdonalds regional 
marketing manager in milwaukee 
they were looking for a convenient portable sandwich for 
football games and other activities ms koepke said 
many of the mcdonalds staples came about in response to 
customer needs she said for instance the big mac was first sold 
in industrial areas of philadelphia where workers wanted a bigger 
sandwich she said 
the new sub was developed in conjunction with oscar mayer co 
which has its headquarters in madison and supplies the meats in the 
sandwich ms koepke said 
its a small test operation but it holds the possibility for 
some more business oscar mayer spokesman jim aehl said 
the five flavors of a mcsub vegetarian italian ham and 
cheese turkey and turkey combo range in price from 199 to 
259 the come in an eightinch bun and with the standard 
submarine fixings of tomatoes lettuce onions and special sauces 
it is a very popular item ms koepke said but it is too 
early to tell whether we will roll it out nationally we tested the 
chicken mcnuggets for 10 years before we took it national 
</TEXT>
