<TEXT>
kuwaitis have spent 564 million for a public 
relations firm to promote the countrys cause after the iraqi 
invasion on aug 2 justice department records show 
the money was paid to hill amp knowlton inc for the period aug 
20nov 10 according to records the firm filed with the foreign 
agents registration office 
frank mankiewicz a senior hill amp knowlton executive said 
wednesday that kuwaits account was for a big job on a big stage 
the assignment is to be effective 
hill amp knowlton disbursed 27 million of the 564 million 
including 644571 for video production and 140412 for travel 
citizens for a free kuwait a group that receives most of its 
money from the kuwait governmentinexile hired hill amp knowlton to 
provide counsel on a national media program strategic planning 
and message development the records said 
the public relations firm helped arrange national free kuwait 
day set up interviews for reporters in the united states and saudi 
arabia contacted government officials and educators and drafted 
and disseminated mailings to congress on the persian gulf crisis 
and human rights issues 
since the invasion kuwaits governmentinexile which is based 
in taif saudi arabia has attempted to draw international 
attention to the situation inside kuwait particularly the 
purported atrocities committed by iraqi troops 
hassan alebraheem president of the citizens group said it has 
spent a lot of money on the public relations campaign but would 
you not do the same for your own country 
the 564 million hill amp knowlton received from kuwait was by 
far the largest amount the company was paid by any foreign entity 
for the sixmonth period the next largest amount was 189 million 
paid by mazda motor corp 
mankiewicz 138 people were registered on the kuwait account but 
a core group of 75 people spent most of the time on it 
rep james a hayes dla said he was distressed by the money 
paid by a foreign entity to a public relations firm 
he said he believed it was wrong for a public relations firm to 
be in the middle of a foreign policy debate in effect he said 
kuwait which is prohibited from directly contributing to 
congressional campaigns was buying influence through hill amp 
knowlton 
