<TEXT>
pier 1 imports inc lost 17 million 
in the third quarter as sales turned sluggish following the iraqi 
invasion of kuwait 
pier 1s loss of 5 cents a share came on sales of 1457 million 
during the quarter that ended dec 1 during the same quarter a 
year ago pier 1 earned 57 million or 16 cents a share on sales 
of 1313 million 
the sales slump mirrored a drop in business at other retailers 
across the country that followed the iraqi invasion consumers have 
also been spending cautiously because of the weakening economy 
pier 1 said its sales picked up as the holiday shopping season 
began 
for the first nine months of pier 1s fiscal year the company 
said it earned 86 million or 24 cents a share on sales of 
4337 million thats a 56 percent decline from the 1989 
ninemonth profit of 198 million or 55 cents a share on sales 
of 3801 million 
