<TEXT>
shearson lehman brothers inc announced a plan 
wednesday to keep top stockbrokers at the firm by offering up to 
80000 in annual incentives that cant be cashed in for five 
years 
shearson follows merrill lynch amp co in revamping its 
compensation program during a period of slumping retail brokerage 
activity across wall street that has made stockbrokers more willing 
to take other jobs 
under the shearson program brokers and branch managers who have 
completed five years of consecutive service and meet production 
criteria will receive 4 percent of their gross production up to a 
maximum 80000 
after that employees in the program will be eligible for awards 
of 1 percent to 5 percent of gross production annually again up to 
a maximum 80000 a year to qualify brokers must increase their 
production by certain percentages over a previous threeyear 
average 
the brokers cannot receive the money before five years a move 
preventing those who qualify from leaving the firm and taking the 
bonus the cash however will earn interest also shearson said 
it can revoke an award under certain conditions depending on a 
brokers performance 
its golden handcuffs is what it amounts to said lawrence 
eckenfelder an analyst with prudentialbache securities inc in 
san francisco 
when things are slow is when you tend to lose more people 
he said when business is good brokers are always less inclined 
to leave 
for branch managers and brokers with the highest levels of 
production 25 percent of the incentive awards will consist of 
stock in american express co shearsons parent during the 
fiveyear waiting period employees will receive cash dividend 
payments on the stock 
last week merrill lynch said it would give a certificate to 
each of its 10500 brokers that could be worth up to 100000 if 
they remain at the firm for 10 years 
unlike merrill though shearson said it is not changing its 
method of commission payouts that comprise compensation for its 
9000 brokers merrill said newly hired inexperienced brokers 
would receive salaries in their first two years 
its incentive to stay and do quality business and to stay and 
be productive said joseph j plumeri president of shearsons 
private client group it was never on our mind to keep people 
from leaving 
shearson said in a statement it was forming a board that would 
review every award recommendation against a set of guidelines based 
on superior client service integrity quality ethics and 
teamwork the board will consist of senior managers including 
shearson lehman brothers president jonathan s linen 
analysts said the compensation incentives by merrill and 
shearson the nations top two brokerage firms marked a change 
typically wall street firms give annual bonuses to brokers based 
on production levels 
eckenfelder said the programs were cheaper than recruiting 
topflight brokers from other firms with large bonuses he also 
said that reducing attrition among top brokers could help improve 
the firms bottom line 
</TEXT>
