<TEXT>
hewlettpackard co said wendesday it 
has restructured its computer division and expanded its presence in 
the semiconductor test equipment business by agreeing to buy 
applied optoelectronic technology corp 
hewlettpackard which posted 132 billion in revenues in its 
1990 fiscal year also said it will focus more resources on the 
telecommunication market 
hewlettpackards revamping of its computer systems organization 
follows a companywide reorganization of executive responsibilities 
announced oct 5 
under the computer reorganization four groups computer 
systems workstations information networks and engineering 
applications were merged into two groups 
willem p roelandts former general manager of the computer 
systems group heads one of the new groups networked systems the 
group is responsible for developing and marketing workstations 
minicomputers risc technology core networking operating systems 
languages databases and computer integration 
robert j frankenberg former general manager of the information 
networks group heads the new cooperative computing group which is 
responsible for developing and marketing distributed computing 
applications user interfaces and office and personal network 
products 
roelandts and frankenberg will continue to report to lewis e 
platt head of computer systems 
our simplified structure will help us speed products to 
market platt said 
the deal with privately held applied optoelectronic technology 
aot based in milpitas is expected to be completed in late 
january terms were not disclosed 
aot an 11yearold company with under 10 million in 1990 
revenue designs and produces automatic test equipment for 
semiconductor manufacturers the equipment which integrates 
computers and instrumentation tests devices during the 
manufacturing process 
aot also makes systems that test smartpower modules these 
modules incorporate control functions for making decisions and 
power functions for performing tasks such as adjusting the speed 
of a cars motor or activating electronic door locks 
in autos smartpower integrated circuits can regulate antilock 
brakes adjust the suspension based on the weight of passengers and 
sense tire pressure 
robert i chen aots president and founder and a former 
hewlettpackard employee will continue to head the company aot 
which sells systems and instruments to several of the worlds 
leading automotive companies will operate under its own name as a 
division of hewlettpackard 
hewlettpackards acquisition of aot is part of a strategy to 
become a bigger player in semiconductor test equipment 
</TEXT>
