<TEXT>
donald trumps taj mahal hotel and 
casino has to give its financial forecasts for the next five years 
to state gaming regulators the state casino control commission 
ruled wednesday 
the commission said in its ongoing hearings on the financial 
stability of the 8monthold taj mahal that the casino must 
present its monthly forecasts for 1991 and quarterly predictions 
for the years 199295 
the taj mahal must also submit fully executed documents to the 
commission that show how it plans to implement agreements with its 
lenders commission chairman steve perskie said 
perskie said he anticipates conducting the next hearing on the 
taj mahal sometime in january after the commission can study all 
the data the commission has the power to take away a license if it 
finds the casino operator is financially unstable 
trump attorney nicholas ribis said he expected the financial 
forecasts and the documents would be ready by dec 28 
the commissions hearings are looking at the stability of the 
taj mahal which renegotiated its 675 million debt one day after 
failing to make a 473 million payment nov 15 
the casino intends to file a prepackaged bankruptcy under 
chapter 11 of the us bankruptcy code and leave bankruptcy 
protection by spring the taj mahals restructuring would give 
bondholders half ownership in the taj mahal in exchange for 
accepting a lower interest rate 12 percent instead of 14 percent 
