directors of the nations second largest 
independent oil company wednesday abandoned efforts to sell the 
firm because they received no acceptable bids 
insead the board of union texas petroleum holdings inc 
decided to try to sell the companys us onshore and offshore 
exploration and production businesses and its hydrocarbon products 
businesses 
that would leave only the companys international exploration 
and production businesses said spokeswoman carol cox 
a company statement said union texas would also pursue other 
restructuring alternatives but ms cox declined comment on the 
alternatives 
no assurance can be given that the activities will result in 
any transaction a statement from the houstonbased company said 
the announcement briefly halted trading in union texas stock on 
the new york stock exchange union texas stock closed at 15 a 
share wednesday down 1 
union texass board announced april 30 the company was on the 
block and analysts said at the time it could sell for as much as 
225 billion 
if union texas had sold for the expected price of 25 a share 
kohlberg kravis amp roberts a leverage buyout specialist that owns 
40 percent of the company could have earned a profit of about 750 
million on stock bought five years ago at 750 a share 
allied signal inc the aerospace and automotive parts 
conglomerate owns another 40 percent also has said it was 
interested in selling its union texas holdings 
union texas owns 38 percent of the largest natural gas producer 
in indonesia one of the hottest exploration areas in the world it 
also has crude oil production and exploration operations in the 
